<br>
Lets see, Mankind has been on the earth in one form or another for what, 5 million years tops?  For the first 4 million we were incoherent cavemen, little better than apes.  Around 10,000 BC is when the Flood is supposed to have happened.  Mankind only has documented civilization since about 3,000 bc.<br>
<br>
Cockroachs, 300million years and still kicking.<br>
<br>
Sharks, 220million years<br>
<br>
Dinosaurs, 250 million years.<br>
<br>
Mankind is just a blip on the scale of earth, a mere twinkle of the eye.<br>
<br>
I was watching a documentary on the polar ice cap and an amazing thing they found was that the weather on earth has only been stable in the last 10,000 years and that has allowed man to proliferate.<br>
<br>
Imagine a graph showing a crazy up and down pattern for over 10 million years and only in the last 10,000 years has the pattern stablilized.  That would be the weather on earth.  Pretty wild eh?<br>
<br>
So, mans existence, while we think it is all the hotshit, is really just a blip in earths memory.  We aren't all that.   All it would take is one good asteroid or a return to crazy weather and we would be back to the caves. <p>Herder
