<br>
Jesus was one of 4 things.<br>
<br>
1) A Liar.  He wasn't really the son of God, and just pretended.  This is preposterous, because liars don't behave the way he did with such convinction and forthrightness.  If he willingly went to his death, knowing full well he was NOT the messiah and dying as a blood sacrifice for the sins of humanity, it would make him....<br>
<br>
2) Insane.  This is also preposterous.  No insane person acts with the calculating rationality which so marked his words and actions.  His prophecies and predictions to his disciples may have seemed like madness, but when studied after the fact, they seem quite remarkable, even clairvoyant.  <br>
<br>
