<br>
If we wasn't a demon, then there is only one other possibilty<br>
<br>
4) He is who he said he was.  Jesus.  The Son of God, incarnated on earth, and intended to be the blood sacrifice to take the place of all the animals whose blood had been shed to redeem humans.  His sacrifice, should humans accept it, would be the redeeming factor in their salvation.<br>
