<br>
Adam and Eve could have children and their children could marry and reproduce with each other.  After all, they were only one generation away from perfect creation.  However, within them was the sins of their parents (recessive genes) being passed down to their children.<br>
<br>
Today we must be more careful.  Within each of us is a genetic punishment to be passed onto our offspring.  Disease, deformity and degredation are all waiting to be passed to our children as a punishment for original sin.<br>
<br>
