<br>
Let me set something straight first: Im a total non-christian/muslim/hindu or whatever. Im just a person living in the Netherlands.<br>
<br>
God, Allah, whatever you want to call him/her, all their stories are almost similar. I think you can compare it to a language, a country has its own language, but the language in the west of the country doesnt sound the same as the same language in the east. The Koran, The Bible, the main story of these books come to the same point, they are almost similar, but they are not EXACTLY the same, just like the languages i was talking about. I once heared something about fears that everybody has, from the moment you are born. So, 2002 years ago people also had those fears. And the also did 5000 years ago. Imagine. Your a caveman and you see snow for the very first thing in your life. &quot;Ooooo white stuff&quot;. &quot;Omg its just coming out of the air&quot;. Those people probably started finding explanations for those white things coming out of nowhere. Thats when the Gods come in. The Koran/The Bible/Holy Book_01 all describe their gods as almighty beings. Beings who will punish you if your a bad person. They will punish you with war, rain, thunder, disseases, you name it. Those are those fears i was talking about. <br>
If you ask me, but thats just me, Gods are just excuses for things people dont understand, they motivate people with things they really want, -those people <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> pray</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->-. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Opium for the masses</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, religion keeps people motivated, it keeps them going. <br>
<br>
But I dont believe it, <br>
somehow people cant imagine a space that never ends, a time that has no beginning, no end, but I think our world has never been created, it has always been there.  <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=23109>Duerarn Lfg</a><BR>
